True, though one of the defining features of cyberpunk is enormous disparities between the haves and have-nots, exaggerated as a way for the authors to bring attention to aspects of the modern world. Johnny Silverhand has a metal arm because he got drafted and sent to Peru and got his arm blown off in a pointless war to make bankers and stockbrokers rich, not because he thought it would be cool. Barber's stories posit a much less stratified world in which there is a fad for genetic engineering, and there are furries and big-eyed anime-people in addition to baseline humans.
